*duma-2.5.15 (01 Aug 2009)

  01 Aug 2009; Steve Arnold <nerdboy@gentoo.org> +duma-2.5.15.ebuild,
  +files/duma-2.5.15-GNUmakefile.patch:
  Updated to latest version using ebuild and patch contributed by 
  ssuominen with one or two minor enhancements.  Closes bug #275011.

*duma-2.5.14-r1 (01 Apr 2009)

  01 Apr 2009; Steve Arnold <nerdboy@gentoo.org> -duma-2.5.14.ebuild,
  +duma-2.5.14-r1.ebuild:
  Updated latest ~arch to build with current toolchain (bug #262514).
  Based on what this package does, as well as the failures reported in
  the above bug, it doesn't seem appropriate to pass every random set
  of user-supplied CFLAGS.  Feel free to comment with justification
  for specific flags and/or pointers to relevant info.

